DPD Organizational Assessment Session

Apr 09, 2019
5:30PM -7:00PM

 

The mission of the Duluth Police Department is to provide a safe Duluth for all by strengthening relationships and serving in a respectful, caring, and selfless manner. The DPD works towards this mission by regularly engaging with community organizations, businesses, and individual residents. To kick off the Duluth Police Department’s Organizational Assessment, consultants BerryDunn will host two listening forums to gain public feedback about the DPD. During the forum, two questions will be asked:

 

·         What does the DPD do well?

 

·         What does the DPD need to improve upon?

 

The Organizational Assessment includes a community engagement process. It’s important to get feedback from all Duluth residents to ensure their police department is on a path that aligns with our community. The goal of the assessment will work to maximize:

 

·         Community trust

 

·         Customer and stakeholder confidence

 

·         Operational best practices

 

·         Productivity

 

·         Workforce satisfaction

 

The listening sessions will be hosted on two different days:

April 9th

Denfeld High School

401 N 44th Ave W

April 10th

East High School

301 N 40th Ave E

 



 

 

 

 

 

 

 

For those who wish to provide feedback, but are unable to do so in person, there will be an opportunity to provide comment online. As the date gets closer to the community forums, a link will be shared via the City of Duluth website and social media platforms that will bring users to the online form.

 

 

Location:
Denfeld High School
4405 W 4th St, Duluth, MN 55807, USA
Website:
http://www.duluthmn.gov
